---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="HIPAA-Compliant LLM Usage: Protect PHI When Using AI APIs"
  description="Learn how healthcare organizations can use AI APIs while maintaining HIPAA compliance. Mask Protected Health Information (PHI) before it reaches LLMs with AI Privacy Gateway. Deploy in 30 seconds."
  keywords="HIPAA AI合规,医疗数据AI保护,PHI保护LLM,健康信息隐私AI,医疗AI数据安全合规"
  canonicalURL="https://privacygw.pages.dev/hipaa-llm-security"
  ogType="article"
  hreflang={[
    { lang: 'zh-CN', url: 'https://privacygw.pages.dev/hipaa-llm-security' },
    { lang: 'x-default', url: 'https://privacygw.pages.dev/hipaa-llm-security' },
  ]}>
  <Nav />

  <section class="seo-page">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="seo-header">
        <div class="seo-badge">HIPAA Compliance Guide</div>
        <h1>HIPAA-Compliant LLM Usage: Protect Patient Data When Using AI</h1>
        <p class="seo-subtitle">
          Healthcare organizations are adopting AI tools at record speed, but sending Protected
          Health Information (PHI) to third-party AI APIs creates significant HIPAA risk.
          AI Privacy Gateway masks PHI before it leaves your infrastructure, enabling safe and
          compliant LLM usage.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="seo-tldr glass">
        <strong>TL;DR:</strong> Every time a healthcare provider pastes patient data into an AI
        tool, PHI leaves their control. AI Privacy Gateway automatically detects and masks PHI
        (names, medical record numbers, phone numbers, addresses, etc.) before it reaches the AI
        API. Deploy as a local proxy in 30 seconds.
      </div>

      <h2>HIPAA and AI APIs: The Compliance Challenge</h2>

      <p>
        Under HIPAA, covered entities and business associates must ensure that Protected Health
        Information (PHI) is safeguarded when shared with third parties. Using AI APIs presents
        several challenges:
      </p>

      <div class="phi-grid">
        <div class="phi-card glass">
          <h3>&#10007; No Business Associate Agreement (BAA)</h3>
          <p>Many AI API providers do not offer BAAs, or only offer them for enterprise plans. Without a BAA, sending PHI to an AI API violates HIPAA.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="phi-card glass">
          <h3>&#10007; Data De-identification Required</h3>
          <p>HIPAA's Safe Harbor method requires removing 18 specific identifiers from PHI. Manual de-identification is error-prone and time-consuming.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="phi-card glass">
          <h3>&#10007; No Audit Trail</h3>
          <p>Standard AI API usage lacks the access logs, disclosure tracking, and audit controls required by HIPAA.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="phi-card glass">
          <h3>&#10007; Data Retention Risk</h3>
          <p>AI providers may retain prompts for model improvement. HIPAA requires defined data retention and destruction policies.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2>The 18 HIPAA Identifiers: How the Gateway Handles Them</h2>
      <p>
        The gateway automatically detects and masks the 18 HIPAA-designated identifiers before
        they reach the AI API:
      </p>

      <div class="identifiers-grid">
        <div class="identifier-item"><span class="id-chip id-covered">Names</span> Patient and family member names</div>
        <div class="identifier-item"><span class="id-chip id-covered">Phone</span> Telephone numbers</div>
        <div class="identifier-item"><span class="id-chip id-covered">Email</span> Email addresses</div>
        <div class="identifier-item"><span class="id-chip id-covered">Address</span> Street address, city, county, ZIP</div>
        <div class="identifier-item"><span class="id-chip id-covered">SSN</span> Social Security Numbers</div>
        <div class="identifier-item"><span class="id-chip id-covered">MRN</span> Medical record numbers</div>
        <div class="identifier-item"><span class="id-chip id-covered">Health Plan</span> Health plan beneficiary numbers</div>
        <div class="identifier-item"><span class="id-chip id-covered">Account</span> Account numbers</div>
        <div class="identifier-item"><span class="id-chip id-covered">License</span> License plate numbers</div>
        <div class="identifier-item"><span class="id-chip id-covered">Device</span> Device identifiers and serial numbers</div>
        <div class="identifier-item"><span class="id-chip id-covered">URL</span> Web URLs</div>
        <div class="identifier-item"><span class="id-chip id-covered">IP</span> IP addresses</div>
        <div class="identifier-item"><span class="id-chip id-covered">Biometric</span> Biometric identifiers (custom rule)</div>
        <div class="identifier-item"><span class="id-chip id-covered">Photos</span> Full-face photos (custom rule)</div>
        <div class="identifier-item"><span class="id-chip id-extra">Dates</span> Dates of birth, admission, discharge</div>
        <div class="identifier-item"><span class="id-chip id-extra">Age</span> Ages over 89 (custom rule)</div>
      </div>

      <div class="phi-note glass">
        <strong>Note:</strong> The gateway covers 14 identifiers out-of-the-box. The remaining
        4 identifiers (biometric data, photos, etc.) can be protected with custom regex rules.
        The gateway's custom rules system lets you add any PHI pattern specific to your healthcare
        organization.
      </div>

      <h2>How AI Privacy Gateway Enables HIPAA-Compliant LLM Use</h2>

      <div class="diagram-flow glass">
        <div class="diagram-row">
          <div class="diagram-node">Clinician App</div>
          <div class="diagram-arrow">&rarr;</div>
          <div class="diagram-node diagram-accent">Privacy Gateway<br/>(PHI masker)</div>
          <div class="diagram-arrow">&rarr;</div>
          <div class="diagram-node diagram-alt">AI API<br/>(de-identified data)</div>
        </div>
        <div class="diagram-row-sub">
          <span class="diagram-check">&#10003; PHI removed before transmission</span>
          <span class="diagram-check">&#10003; No BAA required for masked data</span>
          <span class="diagram-check">&#10003; Full audit trail of masking events</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h3>How De-identification Works</h3>
      <p>
        The gateway implements a HIPAA-compliant de-identification workflow:
      </p>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Detection:</strong> Regex + NER dual engine scans every request for the 18 HIPAA identifiers</li>
        <li><strong>Masking:</strong> Each identifier is replaced with an anonymous placeholder (e.g., <code>[PATIENT_NAME_1]</code>, <code>[PHONE_1]</code>)</li>
        <li><strong>Forwarding:</strong> Only de-identified data reaches the AI API — no PHI transmitted</li>
        <li><strong>Restoration (optional):</strong> If needed, the gateway can restore placeholders in the AI response with original values, but only on your local machine</li>
      </ol>

      <h2>Setup Guide for Healthcare Organizations</h2>

      <div class="code-block glass">
        <div class="code-block-title">Docker (HIPAA-compliant local deployment)</div>
        <pre><code>docker run -d \
  --name ai-privacy-gw \
  -p 9999:9999 \
  -v ./vault_data:/app/vault_data \
  -e TARGET_LLM=https://api.openai.com \
  ghcr.io/gunxueqiu6/ai-privacy-gateway:lite</code></pre>
      </div>

      <p>
        For healthcare deployments, we recommend running the gateway on-premise or in a
        HIPAA-compliant cloud environment. Configure your AI API clients to use
        <code>http://localhost:9999/v1</code> as the base URL.
      </p>

      <h3>Adding Custom PHI Patterns</h3>
      <p>
        Healthcare organizations often have facility-specific PHI patterns (internal MRN formats,
        facility codes, etc.). The gateway's admin dashboard lets you add custom regex rules
        without restarting:
      </p>

      <div class="code-block glass">
        <div class="code-block-title">Custom Rule Examples</div>
        <pre><code># Medical Record Number pattern
Pattern: MRN-\d{7}
Type: Custom PHI
Placeholder: [MRN_1]

# Internal Facility Code
Pattern: FAC-\w{4}-\d{3}
Type: Custom PHI
Placeholder: [FACILITY_1]</code></pre>
      </div>

      <!-- FAQ -->
      <div class="seo-faq glass" id="faq">
        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>Does masking PHI remove the need for a BAA with the AI provider?</h3>
          <p>If PHI is properly de-identified according to HIPAA's Safe Harbor method (removing all 18 identifiers), the resulting data is no longer considered PHI and a BAA may not be required. However, you should consult with your compliance team to confirm your specific use case.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>Is the gateway itself HIPAA-compliant?</h3>
          <p>The gateway is a tool to help you achieve HIPAA compliance, not a certified solution. It provides the technical safeguards required by HIPAA — access controls, encryption at rest, audit logging, and automatic PHI de-identification. You should still conduct a risk assessment and implement appropriate administrative safeguards.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>Can I deploy this in a HIPAA-compliant cloud environment?</h3>
          <p>Yes. The gateway runs on any infrastructure. Deploy it in your HIPAA-compliant AWS, Azure, or GCP environment. The gateway itself is stateless and can be deployed behind a VPN or private network.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>Does it work with medical AI tools like scribes or CDSS?</h3>
          <p>Yes. Any tool that makes API calls to an LLM can be routed through the gateway. This includes AI scribes, clinical decision support systems, medical coding tools, and patient communication platforms.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>How is the vault data encrypted?</h3>
          <p>The SQLite vault is encrypted using AES-256-GCM. The encryption key is auto-generated on first start and stored locally. You can also set your own key via the <code>VAULT_ENCRYPT_KEY</code> environment variable.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>Can I audit what PHI was masked?</h3>
          <p>Yes. The admin dashboard provides real-time masking statistics and a searchable log of detected entities. For HIPAA audit purposes, you can export masking logs from the dashboard.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- CTA -->
      <div class="seo-cta">
        <h2>Deploy HIPAA-Compliant LLM Access</h2>
        <p>Mask PHI automatically. Keep patient data private. Deploy in 30 seconds.</p>
        <div class="seo-cta-buttons">
          <a href="/download" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">Get Started Free</a>
          <a href="/demo" class="btn btn-ghost btn-lg">Try the Demo</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- FAQ Schema -->
      <script type="application/ld+json">{
        "@context": "https://schema.org",
        "@type": "FAQPage",
        "mainEntity": [
          { "@type": "Question", "name": "Does masking PHI remove the need for a BAA?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "If PHI is properly de-identified via Safe Harbor (removing all 18 identifiers), the data may no longer be PHI and a BAA may not be required. Consult your compliance team." } },
          { "@type": "Question", "name": "Is the gateway itself HIPAA-compliant?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "The gateway provides technical safeguards including encryption, access control, audit logging, and automatic PHI de-identification." } },
          { "@type": "Question", "name": "Can I deploy this in a HIPAA-compliant cloud?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes. Deploy in AWS, Azure, or GCP behind a VPN or private network." } }
        ]
      }</script>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  .seo-page { padding: 8rem 0 4rem; }
  .seo-page .container { max-width: 820px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .seo-header { margin-bottom: 3rem; }
  .seo-badge {
    display: inline-block; padding: 0.35rem 0.85rem; border-radius: 20px;
    font-size: 0.78rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--primary);
    background: rgba(134, 239, 172, 0.08); border: 1px solid rgba(134, 239, 172, 0.15);
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }
  .seo-page h1 { font-size: 2.75rem; font-weight: 800; letter-spacing: -0.04em; line-height: 1.15; margin-bottom: 1.25rem; }
  .seo-subtitle { font-size: 1.1rem; color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.8; }
  .seo-tldr { padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 2.5rem; font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--text-primary); }
  .seo-tldr strong { color: var(--primary); }
  .seo-tldr code { background: var(--bg-deep); padding: 0.15rem 0.4rem; border-radius: 4px; font-size: 0.85rem; font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; }
  .seo-page h2 { font-size: 1.8rem; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: -0.03em; margin: 3rem 0 1rem; padding-bottom: 0.5rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .seo-page h3 { font-size: 1.25rem; font-weight: 600; margin: 2rem 0 0.75rem; }
  .seo-page p { color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 1.25rem; }
  .seo-page ul { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
  .seo-page ul li { padding: 0.5rem 0 0.5rem 1.5rem; position: relative; color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.6; }
  .seo-page ul li::before { content: ''; position: absolute; left: 0; top: 0.9rem; width: 6px; height: 6px; border-radius: 50%; background: var(--primary); opacity: 0.5; }
  .seo-page ol { color: var(--text-secondary); margin-bottom: 1.5rem; padding-left: 1.5rem; }
  .seo-page ol li { margin-bottom: 0.75rem; line-height: 1.6; }
  .seo-page a { color: var(--primary); text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 2px; }
  .seo-page a:hover { color: var(--accent); }

  .phi-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 1rem; margin-bottom: 2.5rem; }
  .phi-card { padding: 1.5rem; }
  .phi-card h3 { margin: 0 0 0.5rem; font-size: 1rem; }
  .phi-card p { margin: 0; font-size: 0.88rem; line-height: 1.7; }

  .identifiers-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 0.65rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
  .identifier-item { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.65rem; font-size: 0.88rem; color: var(--text-secondary); }
  .id-chip { font-size: 0.65rem; font-weight: 700; padding: 0.2rem 0.45rem; border-radius: 4px; text-transform: uppercase; white-space: nowrap; }
  .id-covered { background: rgba(134, 239, 172, 0.12); color: var(--primary); }
  .id-extra { background: rgba(251, 191, 36, 0.12); color: #fbbf24; }

  .phi-note { padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 2.5rem; font-size: 0.9rem; line-height: 1.7; }
  .phi-note strong { color: var(--primary); }

  .diagram-flow { padding: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 2.5rem; }
  .diagram-row { display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; gap: 0.75rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .diagram-row-sub { display: flex; justify-content: center; gap: 1.5rem; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .diagram-check { font-size: 0.88rem; color: var(--primary); font-weight: 500; }
  .diagram-node { padding: 0.6rem 1.25rem; border-radius: 10px; font-size: 0.85rem; font-weight: 600; background: rgba(134, 239, 172, 0.06); border: 1px solid var(--border); color: var(--primary); }
  .diagram-accent { color: var(--accent); background: rgba(167, 139, 250, 0.06); }
  .diagram-alt { color: var(--danger); background: rgba(248, 113, 113, 0.06); }
  .diagram-arrow { font-size: 1.25rem; color: var(--text-muted); }

  .code-block { padding: 1.25rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
  .code-block-title { font-size: 0.78rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-muted); margin-bottom: 0.75rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; }
  .code-block pre { margin: 0; font-size: 0.85rem; line-height: 1.7; overflow-x: auto; }
  .code-block code { color: var(--primary); font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; }

  .seo-faq { padding: 2rem; margin-bottom: 3rem; }
  .seo-faq h2 { border: none; margin-top: 0; }
  .faq-item { padding: 1rem 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .faq-item:last-child { border: none; }
  .faq-item h3 { margin: 0 0 0.5rem; font-size: 1.05rem; color: var(--text-primary); }
  .faq-item p { margin: 0; font-size: 0.92rem; }

  .seo-cta { text-align: center; padding: 3rem 2rem; background: var(--glass-bg); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 20px; margin-top: 3rem; }
  .seo-cta h2 { margin-top: 0; border: none; }
  .seo-cta p { color: var(--text-secondary); margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
  .seo-cta-buttons { display: flex; gap: 1rem; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap; }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .seo-page { padding: 6rem 0 3rem; }
    .seo-page h1 { font-size: 2rem; }
    .seo-page h2 { font-size: 1.4rem; }
    .phi-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .identifiers-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .diagram-row { flex-direction: column; gap: 0.5rem; }
  }
  @media (max-width: 639px) {
    .seo-page h1 { font-size: 1.75rem; }
    .seo-cta-buttons { flex-direction: column; }
    .seo-cta-buttons .btn { width: 100%; }
  }
</style>
